I see a few problems with this.  First this error
`A component is changing a controlled input of type text to be uncontrolled (useEffect)` 
doesn&#39;t mean that your value is undefined.  It means your component is trying to change the input to an uncontrolled input.

Second, if `props.loading` is set by a redux saga/thunk, etc when you call `props.onFetched()` and you don&#39;t have any limits or verification in place it will create an infinite loop in your `useEffect`

```
useEffect(() =&gt; {
    props.onFetched();

    setFormData({
      company:
        props.loading || !props.profile.company ? &quot;&quot; : props.profile.company,
    });
  }, [props.loading]);
```

Third, you really shouldn&#39;t `setState` based on props.  If your input component needs the value of `props.profile.company` just use that prop directly.  Like this:

```
 &lt;input
            type=&quot;text&quot;
            placeholder=&quot;Company&quot;
            name=&quot;company&quot;
            value={props.profile.company}
            onChange={e =&gt; onChangeHandler(e)}
          /&gt;
```

